OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F364A1772457071
OL,3,CBoos at Leeds v Man City during
OL,4,CRamadan pause 'massively disappointing'
OL,6,FAn anti-racism and discrimination
OL,7,Forganisation has condemned booing
OL,8,Fheard at Elland Road after a Ramadan
OL,9,Fbreak during Leeds United's Premier
OL,10,FLeague match against Manchester City
OL,11,Fon Saturday.
OL,13,FKick it Out said the response was
OL,14,F"massively disappointing."
OL,16,FPlay was briefly paused in the 13th
OL,17,Fminute under a pre-arranged protocol
OL,18,Fto allow Manchester City's Muslim
OL,19,Fplayers observing Ramadan to break
OL,20,Ftheir fast.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G1/4
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,365,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F364A1772457071
OL,3,CBoos at Leeds v Man City during
OL,4,CRamadan pause 'massively disappointing'
OL,6,FA message was displayed on the
OL,7,Fscoreboard in the stadium which read:
OL,8,F"As tonight's match takes place inside
OL,9,Fthe holy month of Ramadan, play has
OL,10,Fbeen paused briefly to allow players
OL,11,Fto break their fast."
OL,13,FHowever, loud jeers were heard around
OL,14,Fthe ground.
OL,16,FCity had three Muslim players on the
OL,17,Fpitch - Rayan Cherki, Rayan Ait-Nouri
OL,18,Fand Omar Marmoush - and Abdukodir
OL,19,FKhusanov on the bench.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G2/4
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,365,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F364A1772457071
OL,3,CBoos at Leeds v Man City during
OL,4,CRamadan pause 'massively disappointing'
OL,6,FPausing the game to allow Muslim
OL,7,Fplayers to break their fast during the
OL,8,Fholy month has been an agreed protocol
OL,9,Ffor several years.
OL,11,FKick It Out said the crowd reaction
OL,12,Fshows there is "still a long way for
OL,13,Ffootball to go."
OL,15,F"It's an important and visible part of
OL,16,Fmaking the game welcoming for Muslim
OL,17,Fplayers and communities. But as
OL,18,Ftonight's reaction shows, football
OL,19,Fstill has a long way to go in terms of
OL,20,Feducation and acceptance."
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G3/4
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
